2585  )
2586  or EXISTS(self.telephone_number)
2587  )
2588  or EXISTS(self.electronic_mail_address)
2589  ) or EXISTS(self.telex_number)

2591  raise AssertionError("Rule wr1 violated")

16231 def gbsf_check_curve(
16232  cv,
16233 ):
16234  """
16235  :param cv
16236  :type cv:curve
16237  """
16238  if (
16239  SIZEOF(
16240  [
16241  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.BOUNDED_CURVE",
16242  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.CONIC",
16243  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.CURVE_REPLICA",
16244  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.LINE",
16245  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.OFFSET_CURVE_3D",
16246  ]
16247  * TYPEOF(cv)
16248  )
16249  > 1
16250  ):
16251  return FALSE
16252  else:
16253  if (
16254  SIZEOF(["CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.CIRCLE", "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.ELLIPSE"] * TYPEOF(cv))
16255  == 1
16256  ):
16257  return TRUE
16258  else:
16259  if (
16260  ("CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.B_SPLINE_CURVE" == TYPEOF(cv))
16261  and (cv.b_spline_curve.self_intersect == FALSE)
16262  ) or (cv.b_spline_curve.self_intersect == UNKNOWN):
16263  return TRUE
16264  else:
16265  if (
16266  ("CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.COMPOSITE_CURVE" == TYPEOF(cv))
16267  and (cv.composite_curve.self_intersect == FALSE)
16268  ) or (cv.composite_curve.self_intersect == UNKNOWN):
16269  return SIZEOF(None) == 0
16270  else:
16271  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.CURVE_REPLICA" == TYPEOF(cv):
16272  return gbsf_check_curve(cv.curve_replica.parent_curve)
16273  else:
16274  if (
16275  ("CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.OFFSET_CURVE_3D" == TYPEOF(cv))
16276  and (
16277  (cv.offset_curve_3d.self_intersect == FALSE)
16278  or (cv.offset_curve_3d.self_intersect == UNKNOWN)
16279  )
16280  ) and (not ("CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.POLYLINE" == TYPEOF(cv.basis_curve))):
16281  return gbsf_check_curve(cv.offset_curve_3d.basis_curve)
16282  else:
16283  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.PCURVE" == TYPEOF(cv):
16284  return gbsf_check_curve(
16285  cv.pcurve.reference_to_curve.representation.items[1]
16286  ) and gbsf_check_surface(cv.pcurve.basis_surface)
16287  else:
16288  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.POLYLINE" == TYPEOF(cv):
16289  if SIZEOF(cv.polyline.points) >= 3:
16290  return TRUE
16291  else:
16292  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.SURFACE_CURVE" == TYPEOF(cv):
16293  if gbsf_check_curve(cv.surface_curve.curve_3d):
16294  for i in range(
16295  1, SIZEOF(cv.surface_curve.associated_geometry), 1
16296  ):
16297  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.SURFACE" == TYPEOF(
16298  cv.surface_curve.associated_geometry[i]
16299  ):
16300  if not gbsf_check_surface(
16301  cv.surface_curve.associated_geometry[i]
16302  ):
16303  return FALSE
16304  else:
16305  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.PCURVE" == TYPEOF(
16306  cv.surface_curve.associated_geometry[i]
16307  ):
16308  if not gbsf_check_curve(
16309  cv.surface_curve.associated_geometry[i]
16310  ):
16311  return FALSE
16312  return TRUE
16313  else:
16314  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.TRIMMED_CURVE" == TYPEOF(cv):
16315  if (
16316  SIZEOF(
16317  [
16318  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.LINE",
16319  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.PARABOLA",
16320  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.HYPERBOLA",
16321  ]
16322  * TYPEOF(cv.trimmed_curve.basis_curve)
16323  )
16324  == 1
16325  ):
16326  return TRUE
16327  else:
16328  return gbsf_check_curve(
16329  cv.trimmed_curve.basis_curve
16330  )
16331  return FALSE

16354 def base_axis(
16355  dim,
16356  axis1,
16357  axis2,
16358  axis3,
16359 ):
16360  """
16361  :param dim
16362  :type dim:INTEGER
16363  :param axis1
16364  :type axis1:direction
16365  :param axis2
16366  :type axis2:direction
16367  :param axis3
16368  :type axis3:direction
16369  """
16370  if dim == 3:
16371  d1 = NVL(normalise(axis3), dummy_gri == direction([0, 0, 1]))
16372  d2 = first_proj_axis(d1, axis1)
16373  u = [d2, second_proj_axis(d1, d2, axis2), d1]
16374  else:
16375  if EXISTS(axis1):
16376  d1 = normalise(axis1)
16377  u = [d1, orthogonal_complement(d1)]
16378  if EXISTS(axis2):
16379  factor = dot_product(axis2, u[2])
16380  if factor < 0:
16381  u[2].direction_ratios[1] = -u[2].direction_ratios[1]
16382  u[2].direction_ratios[2] = -u[2].direction_ratios[2]
16383  else:
16384  if EXISTS(axis2):
16385  d1 = normalise(axis2)
16386  u = [orthogonal_complement(d1), d1]
16387  u[1].direction_ratios[1] = -u[1].direction_ratios[1]
16388  u[1].direction_ratios[2] = -u[1].direction_ratios[2]
16389  else:
16390  u = [dummy_gri == direction([1, 0]), dummy_gri == direction([0, 1])]
16391  return u

16397 def get_basis_surface(
16398  c,
16399 ):
16400  """
16401  :param c
16402  :type c:curve_on_surface
16403  """
16404  surfs = []
16405  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.PCURVE" == TYPEOF(c):
16406  surfs = [c.pcurve.basis_surface]
16407  else:
16408  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.SURFACE_CURVE" == TYPEOF(c):
16409  n = SIZEOF(c.surface_curve.associated_geometry)
16410  for i in range(1, n, 1):
16411  surfs = surfs + associated_surface(c.surface_curve.associated_geometry[i])
16412  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.COMPOSITE_CURVE_ON_SURFACE" == TYPEOF(c):
16413  n = SIZEOF(c.composite_curve.segments)
16414  surfs = get_basis_surface(c.composite_curve.segments[1].parent_curve)
16415  if n > 1:
16416  for i in range(2, n, 1):
16417  surfs = surfs * get_basis_surface(c.composite_curve.segments[i].parent_curve)
16418  return surfs

16627 def first_proj_axis(
16628  z_axis,
16629  arg,
16630 ):
16631  """
16632  :param z_axis
16633  :type z_axis:direction
16634  :param arg
16635  :type arg:direction
16636  """
16637  if not EXISTS(z_axis):
16638  return None
16639  else:
16640  z = normalise(z_axis)
16641  if not EXISTS(arg):
16642  if z.direction_ratios != [1, 0, 0]:
16643  v = dummy_gri == direction([1, 0, 0])
16644  else:
16645  v = dummy_gri == direction([0, 1, 0])
16646  else:
16647  if arg.dim != 3:
16648  return None
16649  if cross_product(arg, z).magnitude == 0:
16650  return None
16651  else:
16652  v = normalise(arg)
16653  x_vec = scalar_times_vector(dot_product(v, z), z)
16654  x_axis = vector_difference(v, x_vec).orientation
16655  x_axis = normalise(x_axis)
16656  return x_axis

16837 def vector_difference(
16838  arg1,
16839  arg2,
16840 ):
16841  """
16842  :param arg1
16843  :type arg1:vector_or_direction
16844  :param arg2
16845  :type arg2:vector_or_direction
16846  """
16847  if ((not EXISTS(arg1)) or (not EXISTS(arg2))) or (arg1.dim != arg2.dim):
16848  return None
16849  else:
16850  # begin/end block
16851  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.VECTOR" == TYPEOF(arg1):
16852  mag1 = arg1.magnitude
16853  vec1 = arg1.orientation
16854  else:
16855  mag1 = 1
16856  vec1 = arg1
16857  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.VECTOR" == TYPEOF(arg2):
16858  mag2 = arg2.magnitude
16859  vec2 = arg2.orientation
16860  else:
16861  mag2 = 1
16862  vec2 = arg2
16863  vec1 = normalise(vec1)
16864  vec2 = normalise(vec2)
16865  ndim = SIZEOF(vec1.direction_ratios)
16866  mag = 0
16867  res = dummy_gri == direction(vec1.direction_ratios)
16868  for i in range(1, ndim, 1):
16869  res.direction_ratios[i] = (mag1 * vec1.direction_ratios[i]) + (
16870  mag2 * vec2.direction_ratios[i]
16871  )
16872  mag = mag + (res.direction_ratios[i] * res.direction_ratios[i])
16873  if mag > 0:
16874  result = dummy_gri == vector(res, SQRT(mag))
16875  else:
16876  result = dummy_gri == vector(vec1, 0)
16877  return result

16902  ):
16903  return FALSE
16904  return TRUE

16944 def valid_calendar_date(
16945  date,
16946 ):
16947  """
16948  :param date
16949  :type date:calendar_date
16950  """
16951  if not ((1 <= date.day_component) and (date.day_component <= 31)):
16952  return FALSE
16953  case_selector = date.month_component
16954  if case_selector == 4:
16955  return (1 <= date.day_component) and (date.day_component <= 30)
16956  elif case_selector == 6:
16957  return (1 <= date.day_component) and (date.day_component <= 30)
16958  elif case_selector == 9:
16959  return (1 <= date.day_component) and (date.day_component <= 30)
16960  elif case_selector == 11:
16961  return (1 <= date.day_component) and (date.day_component <= 30)
16962  elif case_selector == 2:
16963  # begin/end block
16964  if leap_year(date.year_component):
16965  return (1 <= date.day_component) and (date.day_component <= 29)
16966  else:
16967  return (1 <= date.day_component) and (date.day_component <= 28)
16968  else:
16969  return TRUE

17114 def scalar_times_vector(
17115  scalar,
17116  vec,
17117 ):
17118  """
17119  :param scalar
17120  :type scalar:REAL
17121  :param vec
17122  :type vec:vector_or_direction
17123  """
17124  if (not EXISTS(scalar)) or (not EXISTS(vec)):
17125  return None
17126  else:
17127  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.VECTOR" == TYPEOF(vec):
17128  v = dummy_gri == direction(vec.orientation.direction_ratios)
17129  mag = scalar * vec.magnitude
17130  else:
17131  v = dummy_gri == direction(vec.direction_ratios)
17132  mag = scalar
17133  if mag < 0:
17134  for i in range(1, SIZEOF(v.direction_ratios), 1):
17135  v.direction_ratios[i] = -v.direction_ratios[i]
17136  mag = -mag
17137  result = dummy_gri == vector(normalise(v), mag)
17138  return result

17144 def dimensions_for_si_unit(
17145  n,

17147  """
17148  :param n

17150  """

17155  return dimensional_exponents(0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0)
17156  elif case_selector == second:
17157  return dimensional_exponents(0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0)
17158  elif case_selector == ampere:
17159  return dimensional_exponents(0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0)
17160  elif case_selector == kelvin:
17161  return dimensional_exponents(0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0)
17162  elif case_selector == mole:
17163  return dimensional_exponents(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0)

17165  return dimensional_exponents(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1)

17167  return dimensional_exponents(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0)

17169  return dimensional_exponents(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0)

17171  return dimensional_exponents(0, 0, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0)

17173  return dimensional_exponents(1, 1, -2, 0, 0, 0, 0)

17297 def gbsf_check_surface(
17298  sf,
17299 ):
17300  """
17301  :param sf
17302  :type sf:surface
17303  """
17304  if (
17305  ("CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.B_SPLINE_SURFACE" == TYPEOF(sf))
17306  and (sf.b_spline_surface.self_intersect == FALSE)
17307  ) or (sf.b_spline_surface.self_intersect == UNKNOWN):
17308  return TRUE
17309  else:
17310  if (
17311  SIZEOF(
17312  [
17313  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.SPHERICAL_SURFACE",
17314  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.TOROIDAL_SURFACE",
17315  ]
17316  * TYPEOF(sf)
17317  )
17318  == 1
17319  ):
17320  return TRUE
17321  else:
17322  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.CURVE_BOUNDED_SURFACE" == TYPEOF(sf):
17323  if (
17324  SIZEOF(
17325  [
17326  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.CONICAL_SURFACE",
17327  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.CYLINDRICAL_SURFACE",
17328  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.PLANE",
17329  ]
17330  * TYPEOF(sf.curve_bounded_surface.basis_surface)
17331  )
17332  == 1
17333  ):
17334  return SIZEOF(None) == 0
17335  else:
17336  if gbsf_check_surface(sf.curve_bounded_surface.basis_surface):
17337  return SIZEOF(None) == 0
17338  else:
17339  if (
17340  ("CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.OFFSET_SURFACE" == TYPEOF(sf))
17341  and (sf.offset_surface.self_intersect == FALSE)
17342  ) or (sf.offset_surface.self_intersect == UNKNOWN):
17343  return gbsf_check_surface(sf.offset_surface.basis_surface)
17344  else:
17345  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.RECTANGULAR_COMPOSITE_SURFACE" == TYPEOF(sf):
17346  for i in range(1, SIZEOF(sf.rectangular_composite_surface.segments), 1):
17347  for j in range(
17348  1, SIZEOF(sf.rectangular_composite_surface.segments[i]), 1
17349  ):
17350  if not gbsf_check_surface(
17351  sf.rectangular_composite_surface.segments[i][j].parent_surface
17352  ):
17353  return FALSE
17354  return TRUE
17355  else:
17356  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.RECTANGULAR_TRIMMED_SURFACE" == TYPEOF(sf):
17357  if (
17358  SIZEOF(
17359  [
17360  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.CONICAL_SURFACE",
17361  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.CYLINDRICAL_SURFACE",
17362  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.PLANE",
17363  ]
17364  * TYPEOF(sf.rectangular_trimmed_surface.basis_surface)
17365  )
17366  == 1
17367  ):
17368  return TRUE
17369  else:
17370  return gbsf_check_surface(
17371  sf.rectangular_trimmed_surface.basis_surface
17372  )
17373  else:
17374  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.SURFACE_REPLICA" == TYPEOF(sf):
17375  return gbsf_check_surface(sf.surface_replica.parent_surface)
17376  else:
17377  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.SWEPT_SURFACE" == TYPEOF(sf):
17378  return gbsf_check_curve(sf.swept_surface.swept_curve)
17379  return FALSE

17418 def normalise(
17419  arg,
17420 ):
17421  """
17422  :param arg
17423  :type arg:vector_or_direction
17424  """
17425  if not EXISTS(arg):
17426  result = None
17427  else:
17428  ndim = arg.dim
17429  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.VECTOR" == TYPEOF(arg):
17430  # begin/end block
17431  v = dummy_gri == direction(arg.orientation.direction_ratios)
17432  if arg.magnitude == 0:
17433  return None
17434  else:
17435  vec = dummy_gri == vector(v, 1)
17436  else:
17437  v = dummy_gri == direction(arg.direction_ratios)
17438  mag = 0
17439  for i in range(1, ndim, 1):
17440  mag = mag + (v.direction_ratios[i] * v.direction_ratios[i])
17441  if mag > 0:
17442  mag = SQRT(mag)
17443  for i in range(1, ndim, 1):
17444  v.direction_ratios[i] = v.direction_ratios[i] / mag
17445  if "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.VECTOR" == TYPEOF(arg):
17446  vec.orientation = v
17447  result = vec
17448  else:
17449  result = v
17450  else:
17451  return None
17452  return result

17467  else:

17616 
17619 def constraints_param_b_spline(
17620  degree,
17621  up_knots,
17622  up_cp,
17623  knot_mult,
17624  knots,
17625 ):
17626  """
17627  :param degree
17628  :type degree:INTEGER
17629  :param up_knots
17630  :type up_knots:INTEGER
17631  :param up_cp
17632  :type up_cp:INTEGER
17633  :param knot_mult
17634  :type knot_mult:(null)
17635  :param knots
17636  :type knots:(null)
17637  """
17638  sum = knot_mult[1]
17639  for i in range(2, up_knots, 1):
17640  sum = sum + knot_mult[i]
17641  if (((degree < 1) or (up_knots < 2)) or (up_cp < degree)) or (sum != ((degree + up_cp) + 2)):
17642  result = FALSE
17643  return result
17644  k = knot_mult[1]
17645  if (k < 1) or (k > (degree + 1)):
17646  result = FALSE
17647  return result
17648  for i in range(2, up_knots, 1):
17649  if (knot_mult[i] < 1) or (knots[i] <= knots[i - 1]):
17650  result = FALSE
17651  return result
17652  k = knot_mult[i]
17653  if (i < up_knots) and (k > degree):
17654  result = FALSE
17655  return result
17656  if (i == up_knots) and (k > (degree + 1)):
17657  result = FALSE
17658  return result
17659  return result

17665 def using_representations(
17666  item,
17667 ):
17668  """
17669  :param item
17670  :type item:founded_item_select
17671  """
17672  results = []
17673  result_bag = USEDIN(item, "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.REPRESENTATION.ITEMS")
17674  if SIZEOF(result_bag) > 0:
17675  for i in range(1, HIINDEX(result_bag), 1):
17676  results = results + result_bag[i]
17677  intermediate_items = using_items(item, [])
17678  if SIZEOF(intermediate_items) > 0:
17679  for i in range(1, HIINDEX(intermediate_items), 1):
17680  result_bag = USEDIN(intermediate_items[i], "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.REPRESENTATION.ITEMS")
17681  if SIZEOF(result_bag) > 0:
17682  for j in range(1, HIINDEX(result_bag), 1):
17683  results = results + result_bag[j]
17684  return results

17728 def cross_product(
17729  arg1,
17730  arg2,
17731 ):
17732  """
17733  :param arg1
17734  :type arg1:direction
17735  :param arg2
17736  :type arg2:direction
17737  """
17738  if (((not EXISTS(arg1)) or (arg1.dim == 2)) or (not EXISTS(arg2))) or (arg2.dim == 2):
17739  return None
17740  else:
17741  # begin/end block
17742  v1 = normalise(arg1).direction_ratios
17743  v2 = normalise(arg2).direction_ratios
17744  res = dummy_gri == direction(
17745  [
17746  (v1[2] * v2[3]) - (v1[3] * v2[2]),
17747  (v1[3] * v2[1]) - (v1[1] * v2[3]),
17748  (v1[1] * v2[2]) - (v1[2] * v2[1]),
17749  ]
17750  )
17751  mag = 0
17752  for i in range(1, 3, 1):
17753  mag = mag + (res.direction_ratios[i] * res.direction_ratios[i])
17754  if mag > 0:
17755  result = dummy_gri == vector(res, SQRT(mag))
17756  else:
17757  result = dummy_gri == vector(arg1, 0)
17758  return result

17847 def constraints_rectangular_composite_surface(
17848  s,
17849 ):
17850  """
17851  :param s
17852  :type s:rectangular_composite_surface
17853  """
17854  for i in range(1, s.n_u, 1):
17855  for j in range(1, s.n_v, 1):
17856  if not (
17857  (
17858  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.B_SPLINE_SURFACE"
17859  == TYPEOF(s.segments[i][j].parent_surface)
17860  )
17861  or (
17862  "CONFIG_CONTROL_DESIGN.RECTANGULAR_TRIMMED_SURFACE"
17863  == TYPEOF(s.segments[i][j].parent_surface)
17864  )
17865  ):
17866  return FALSE
17867  for i in range(1, s.n_u - 1, 1):
17868  for j in range(1, s.n_v, 1):
17869  if s.segments[i][j].u_transition == discontinuous:
17870  return FALSE
17871  for i in range(1, s.n_u, 1):
17872  for j in range(1, s.n_v - 1, 1):
17873  if s.segments[i][j].v_transition == discontinuous:
17874  return FALSE
17875  return TRUE

17996 def dot_product(
17997  arg1,
17998  arg2,
17999 ):
18000  """
18001  :param arg1
18002  :type arg1:direction
18003  :param arg2
18004  :type arg2:direction
18005  """
18006  if (not EXISTS(arg1)) or (not EXISTS(arg2)):
18007  scalar = None
18008  else:
18009  if arg1.dim != arg2.dim:
18010  scalar = None
18011  else:
18012  # begin/end block
18013  vec1 = normalise(arg1)
18014  vec2 = normalise(arg2)
18015  ndim = arg1.dim
18016  scalar = 0
18017  for i in range(1, ndim, 1):
18018  scalar = scalar + (vec1.direction_ratios[i] * vec2.direction_ratios[i])
18019  return scalar
